Invoking the Create Local Variable x hint inside the while loop will place a new variable outside of the'if' block at the top of the method.  This cause an error inside the 'for' loop because it already has a variable named 'a' that now illegally shadows the created variable.. like this:

public void method() {
	List mixedList =getMyList()
	A a  // Hint will add this line  <<<<<<<<<<<<<<
	if (selection.size() >= 2) {
		// make a pruned list of 'A's
		List alist = new ArrayList()
		for (Object o : mixedList) {
			if (o instanceof A) {
				A a = (A) o // Now this line has error <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
				alist.add(kc)
			}
